{'messages': [HumanMessage(content='why is my fridge not cooling properly', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='8e4792f0-297c-47ab-9a15-1eb0adcd5afc'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'function_call': {'name': 'retrieve_context', 'arguments': '{"query": "refrigerator not cooling properly troubleshooting"}'}}, response_metadata={'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'model_name': 'gemini-2.5-flash-lite', 'safety_ratings': [], 'model_provider': 'google_genai'}, id='lc_run--019b34d3-43b3-7930-8e8a-1016c169aa7a-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'retrieve_context', 'args': {'query': 'refrigerator not cooling properly troubleshooting'}, 'id': '8231a8d5-4499-404e-8a3b-ec772af373bf', 'type': 'tool_call'}], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 486, 'output_tokens': 20, 'total_tokens': 506, 'input_token_details': {'cache_read': 0}}), ToolMessage(content="Source: {'page': 49, 'title': 'us_main.book.book', 'author': 'inyou.park', 'source': 'C:\\\\Users\\\\haris\\\\Downloads\\\\Rag\\\\FrenchDoor.pdf', 'creator': 'FrameMaker 2017.0.4', 'moddate': '2021-01-04T10:12:14+09:00', 'producer': 'Acrobat Distiller 20.0 (Windows)', 'page_label': '50', 'total_pages': 68, 'creationdate': '2020-12-28T16:54:51+00:00'}\nContent: 50 TROUBLESHOOTING\nBefore Calling for Service\nReview this section before calling for service; doing so will save you both time and money.\nCooling\nProblem Possible Cause & Solution\nRefrigerator is not \ncooling or has no \npower.\nA fuse in your home may be blown or the circuit breaker tripped. Or the appliance is \nconnected to a GFCI (Ground Fault Circuit Interrupter) outlet, and the outlet's circuit \nbreaker has tripped.\n• Check the main electrical box and replace th e fuse or reset the circuit breaker. Do not \nincrease fuse capacity. If the problem is a circuit overload, have it corrected by a qualified \nelectrician.\n• Reset the circuit breaker on the GFCI. If the problem persists, contact an electrician.\nThe refrigerator control is set to OFF (some models).\n• Turn the control ON. Refer to the Setting th e Controls section for proper temperature \nsettings.\nRefrigerator is set to Demo Mode.\n• Demo Mode allows the lights an d control display to work normally while disabling cooling,\n\nSource: {'page': 49, 'title': 'us_main.book.book', 'author': 'inyou.park', 'source': 'C:\\\\Users\\\\haris\\\\Downloads\\\\Rag\\\\FrenchDoor.pdf', 'creator': 'FrameMaker 2017.0.4', 'moddate': '2021-01-04T10:12:14+09:00', 'producer': 'Acrobat Distiller 20.0 (Windows)', 'page_label': '50', 'total_pages': 68, 'creationdate': '2020-12-28T16:54:51+00:00'}\nContent: 50 TROUBLESHOOTING\nBefore Calling for Service\nReview this section before calling for service; doing so will save you both time and money.\nCooling\nProblem Possible Cause & Solution\nRefrigerator is not \ncooling or has no \npower.\nA fuse in your home may be blown or the circuit breaker tripped. Or the appliance is \nconnected to a GFCI (Ground Fault Circuit Interrupter) outlet, and the outlet's circuit \nbreaker has tripped.\n• Check the main electrical box and replace th e fuse or reset the circuit breaker. Do not \nincrease fuse capacity. If the problem is a circuit overload, have it corrected by a qualified \nelectrician.\n• Reset the circuit breaker on the GFCI. If the problem persists, contact an electrician.\nThe refrigerator control is set to OFF (some models).\n• Turn the control ON. Refer to the Setting th e Controls section for proper temperature \nsettings.\nRefrigerator is set to Demo Mode.\n• Demo Mode allows the lights an d control display to work normally while disabling cooling,", name='retrieve_context', id='4cb45617-9cdd-4310-982d-1f1f8abf946c', tool_call_id='8231a8d5-4499-404e-8a3b-ec772af373bf', artifact=[Document(id='117105dd-8508-45c0-a65c-c95e47f29de9', metadata={'page': 49, 'title': 'us_main.book.book', 'author': 'inyou.park', 'source': 'C:\\Users\\haris\\Downloads\\Rag\\FrenchDoor.pdf', 'creator': 'FrameMaker 2017.0.4', 'moddate': '2021-01-04T10:12:14+09:00', 'producer': 'Acrobat Distiller 20.0 (Windows)', 'page_label': '50', 'total_pages': 68, 'creationdate': '2020-12-28T16:54:51+00:00'}, page_content="50 TROUBLESHOOTING\nBefore Calling for Service\nReview this section before calling for service; doing so will save you both time and money.\nCooling\nProblem Possible Cause & Solution\nRefrigerator is not \ncooling or has no \npower.\nA fuse in your home may be blown or the circuit breaker tripped. Or the appliance is \nconnected to a GFCI (Ground Fault Circuit Interrupter) outlet, and the outlet's circuit \nbreaker has tripped.\n• Check the main electrical box and replace th e fuse or reset the circuit breaker. Do not \nincrease fuse capacity. If the problem is a circuit overload, have it corrected by a qualified \nelectrician.\n• Reset the circuit breaker on the GFCI. If the problem persists, contact an electrician.\nThe refrigerator control is set to OFF (some models).\n• Turn the control ON. Refer to the Setting th e Controls section for proper temperature \nsettings.\nRefrigerator is set to Demo Mode.\n• Demo Mode allows the lights an d control display to work normally while disabling cooling,"), Document(id='43dfce75-5e1b-4a60-b25b-49f2dae6b64c', metadata={'page': 49, 'title': 'us_main.book.book', 'author': 'inyou.park', 'source': 'C:\\Users\\haris\\Downloads\\Rag\\FrenchDoor.pdf', 'creator': 'FrameMaker 2017.0.4', 'moddate': '2021-01-04T10:12:14+09:00', 'producer': 'Acrobat Distiller 20.0 (Windows)', 'page_label': '50', 'total_pages': 68, 'creationdate': '2020-12-28T16:54:51+00:00'}, page_content="50 TROUBLESHOOTING\nBefore Calling for Service\nReview this section before calling for service; doing so will save you both time and money.\nCooling\nProblem Possible Cause & Solution\nRefrigerator is not \ncooling or has no \npower.\nA fuse in your home may be blown or the circuit breaker tripped. Or the appliance is \nconnected to a GFCI (Ground Fault Circuit Interrupter) outlet, and the outlet's circuit \nbreaker has tripped.\n• Check the main electrical box and replace th e fuse or reset the circuit breaker. Do not \nincrease fuse capacity. If the problem is a circuit overload, have it corrected by a qualified \nelectrician.\n• Reset the circuit breaker on the GFCI. If the problem persists, contact an electrician.\nThe refrigerator control is set to OFF (some models).\n• Turn the control ON. Refer to the Setting th e Controls section for proper temperature \nsettings.\nRefrigerator is set to Demo Mode.\n• Demo Mode allows the lights an d control display to work normally while disabling cooling,")]), AIMessage(content='If your refrigerator is not cooling properly, here are a few things to check:\n\n**1. Power Supply:**\n*   **Blown Fuse or Tripped Circuit Breaker:** Check your home\'s main electrical box. If a fuse is blown or a circuit breaker has tripped, replace the fuse or reset the breaker. If the appliance is connected to a GFCI outlet and its breaker has tripped, reset it. If the problem continues, contact an electrician.\n*   **Demo Mode:** Some models have a Demo Mode that disables cooling. Ensure your refrigerator is not in Demo Mode. If it is, turn it off.\n\n**2. Temperature Settings:**\n*   **Control Settings:** Make sure the refrigerator control is not set to OFF. Refer to the "Setting the Controls" section of your owner\'s manual for the correct temperature settings.\n\nIf you have checked these common issues and your refrigerator is still not cooling, it may be necessary to contact LG customer support for further assistance.\n\nSource: us_main.book.book (Page 50)', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'model_name': 'gemini-2.5-flash-lite', 'safety_ratings': [], 'model_provider': 'google_genai'}, id='lc_run--019b34d3-47a5-70d2-b64c-b9abddf79e4b-0', usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 1359, 'output_tokens': 219, 'total_tokens': 1578, 'input_token_details': {'cache_read': 0}})]}

