{'messages': [HumanMessage(content='my fridge is not cooling properly', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='84ec4f7f-de28-4abf-9c61-8308afb4e665'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'function_call': {'name': 'retrieve_context', 'arguments': '{"query": "fridge is not cooling properly"}'}}, response_metadata={'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'model_name': 'gemini-2.5-flash-lite', 'safety_ratings': [], 'model_provider': 'google_genai'}, id='lc_run--019b34d8-ea05-7150-850c-7b4add49aa8b-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'retrieve_context', 'args': {'query': 'fridge is not cooling properly'}, 'id': 'd05b3f18-7b6c-44b0-80e6-d4647c833ee8', 'type': 'tool_call'}], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 485, 'output_tokens': 20, 'total_tokens': 505, 'input_token_details': {'cache_read': 0}}), ToolMessage(content='Source: {\'page\': 51, \'title\': \'us_main.book.book\', \'author\': \'inyou.park\', \'source\': \'C:\\\\Users\\\\haris\\\\Downloads\\\\Rag\\\\FrenchDoor.pdf\', \'creator\': \'FrameMaker 2017.0.4\', \'moddate\': \'2021-01-04T10:12:14+09:00\', \'producer\': \'Acrobat Distiller 20.0 (Windows)\', \'page_label\': \'52\', \'total_pages\': 68, \'creationdate\': \'2020-12-28T16:54:51+00:00\'}\nContent: effect.\nDoors are not closed correctly.\n• See the "Doors will not close correctly or  pop open" section in the Troubleshooting.\nTemperature control is not set correctly.\n• If the temperature is too warm, adjust the control one increment at a time and wait for the \ntemperature to stabilize.\nDefrost cycle has recently completed.\n• During the defrost cycle, the temperature of  each compartment may rise slightly and \ncondensation may form on the back wall. Wait 30 minutes and confirm the proper \ntemperature has been restored once the defrost cycle has completed.\nProblem Possible Cause & Solution', name='retrieve_context', id='2ed4ead2-53ed-40f1-b0d0-7dbcecca05f7', tool_call_id='d05b3f18-7b6c-44b0-80e6-d4647c833ee8', artifact=[Document(id='3b62a311-0fa8-4f78-94b4-cfe415280925', metadata={'page': 51, 'title': 'us_main.book.book', 'author': 'inyou.park', 'source': 'C:\\Users\\haris\\Downloads\\Rag\\FrenchDoor.pdf', 'creator': 'FrameMaker 2017.0.4', 'moddate': '2021-01-04T10:12:14+09:00', 'producer': 'Acrobat Distiller 20.0 (Windows)', 'page_label': '52', 'total_pages': 68, 'creationdate': '2020-12-28T16:54:51+00:00'}, page_content='effect.\nDoors are not closed correctly.\n• See the "Doors will not close correctly or  pop open" section in the Troubleshooting.\nTemperature control is not set correctly.\n• If the temperature is too warm, adjust the control one increment at a time and wait for the \ntemperature to stabilize.\nDefrost cycle has recently completed.\n• During the defrost cycle, the temperature of  each compartment may rise slightly and \ncondensation may form on the back wall. Wait 30 minutes and confirm the proper \ntemperature has been restored once the defrost cycle has completed.\nProblem Possible Cause & Solution')]), AIMessage(content='The following information is available regarding your refrigerator not cooling properly:\n\n**Possible Causes and Solutions:**\n\n*   **Doors are not closed correctly:** Ensure that the refrigerator doors are closing completely. Refer to the "Doors will not close correctly or pop open" section in the Troubleshooting guide for more information.\n*   **Temperature control is not set correctly:** If the temperature feels too warm, adjust the temperature control settings. It is recommended to adjust the control by one increment at a time and allow the temperature to stabilize before making further adjustments.\n*   **Defrost cycle has recently completed:** During the defrost cycle, it is normal for the temperature in each compartment to rise slightly, and condensation may form on the back wall. Wait for approximately 30 minutes, and the proper temperature should be restored after the defrost cycle is complete.\n\nFor further assistance or if these steps do not resolve the issue, please consult the specific troubleshooting section for your model or contact LG customer support.\n\nSource: FrenchDoor.pdf, page 52', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'model_name': 'gemini-2.5-flash-lite', 'safety_ratings': [], 'model_provider': 'google_genai'}, id='lc_run--019b34d8-ed74-7573-a09d-f5811ecd6415-0', usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 834, 'output_tokens': 209, 'total_tokens': 1043, 'input_token_details': {'cache_read': 0}})]}

